*|event=Adolf Koch founded the  (Physical Culture School Adolf Koch). A key figure in the socialist  (free body culture) movement in Germany, he promoted nudity as a means of advancing health, equality, and progressive education. Koch established a network of clothing-free physical education schools, including a large outdoor facility, designed to encourage natural movement, physical well-being, and body confidence|location=Germany.}}
